1. No Custom UI for Existing Components
Before writing any custom HTML for navigation, buttons, tabs, quantity controls, or cards — check if a design system component already exists. If it does, use it. Never reimplement what's already built.

2. No Inline SVGs — Always Use Icon Components
Every icon must come from @/components/icons/. Never write <svg> markup inline. If the icon doesn't exist, add it to the icon library. Applies to buttons, badges, and decorative elements alike.

3. Product Images Must Come From Project Assets
Never use external image URLs (Pexels, Lorem Picsum, etc.) for product images. Use Builder CDN assets, /images/products/ local files, or the PRODUCT_IMAGES helper — whichever already exists in the project.

4. Add-to-Cart Must Be Responsive by Default
WCPAddToCart rendered inside tiles must be size="medium" with label on desktop (>768px) and size="xsmall" icon-only on mobile. This is the default behavior, not an opt-in.

5. Read Component Source Before Using It
Before using any component, read its .tsx file to understand available props (variants, sizes, callbacks). Never guess the API — the source is the source of truth.1. No Custom UI for Existing Components
